## WHO READS WHAT

### Claude Web reads (via Janis's Project Knowledge sync — NOT repo)
- chat_rules.md
- WORKFLOW_SKILL.md

Claude Web NEVER reads directly from repo. cc NEVER reads chat_rules.md
or WORKFLOW_SKILL.md.

### cc reads — EVERY session start (in this order, unless CONTINUATION per
### the CC INTRO self-check in WORKFLOW_SKILL.md's CC PROMPT TEMPLATE)
1. cc_rules.md
2. knowledge.map (this file)
3. cc_chat_log.md (first 3 entries)
4. The task prompt file named in this session

### cc reads — ONLY when the task requires (named explicitly per prompt)
- rules-dimensions.md — any SCAD task
- RULES.md — any SCAD task (numbered R-XXX durable lessons)
- rules-pr.md — PR-01 tasks only
- CURRENT_STATE.md — session resumption / mid-session product switch
- PART_MANIFEST.md (per-project — vending-machine/VM-01-base/,
  vending-machine/VM-02-base/, pilates-reformer/PR-01-base/) — before any
  QA session, before adding any new ASSEMBLY-called module
- design_scope_of_work_rule.md (per-project) — read whenever a session
  confirms a new owner feature/goal, per its own standing rule; NOT on
  cc's automatic session-start list otherwise (confirmed via grep of
  cc_rules.md, VM-01-governance-batch-post-v44 session)
- Every file under /.claude/ — see FILE SYSTEM MAP (/.claude/) below, one
  row each, not summarized as a group

