disconnected thin slivers instead of a continuous band (confirmed via real render, not assumed from the code) — fixed with a real multi-point fan mask (robust to any total sweep angle), re-verified as a clean continuous band via CGAL. v5 kept, UNCHANGED, on record). Previous understructure round: BBQ-understructure-v5.scad (2026-07-20, bbq-understructure-v5-trackwidth-fender-tbar — first understructure round since v4. TASK 0: this file's own `include` FINALLY bumped past v13 to BBQ-chambers-v14.2.scad — the full assembly chain (BBQ-offset-smoker-base-v1.scad -> BBQ-understructure-v5.scad) now actually renders the CURRENT chamber/firebox geometry for the first time since v13; real +50mm chamber_floor_z shift (721.335->771.335mm), front bracket leg re-verified flush against the chamber's real octagon boundary at the new Z via CGAL. TASK 1: ONE shared TRACK_WIDTH=1080mm (FIREBOX_W+2*150+TREAD_W) now drives BOTH front and rear wheel Y-position (retires the independent REAR_TRACK_WIDTH formula + the front caster's own close-set DUAL_WHEEL_OFFSET spacing) — real, CGAL-confirmed: THIS RESOLVES THE STANDING v4 ~6mm FRONT-WHEEL/BRACKET COLLISION (open since 2026-07-17), confirmed via a real intersection() probe returning EMPTY, not assumed. TASK 2: front bracket's forward tow-triangle extension rebuilt round (150mm dia boss via hull(), was a sharp pyramid point). TASK 3: rear wheel repositioned (real 150mm gap to the firebox's own outer-shell edge each side, wheel bottom still real world Z=0) + NEW rear fender per side (150mm real radial clearance arc, welds to the firebox's own outer shell). TASK 4: front U-bracket's own drop length now a live formula (chamber_floor_z-firebox_floor_z=199.935mm, was a 150mm literal), lands exactly at firebox_floor_z; front wheel now a real copy of the rear wheel. TASK 5: front axle rigid single-pivot steering mechanism re-verified (not rebuilt) through the respan, real CGAL steer_deg sweep clean. TASK 6: T-bar length now a live formula (DATU