## GOVERNANCE — NEW PRODUCT DESIGN CONVENTION

Any new product line (not a VM-01/PR-01 continuation) follows one
connected kickoff chain, each step consuming the one before it:

1. **`design_scope_of_work_rule.md`** created for that product FIRST —
   owner-vocabulary features, envelope target, appearance/UX, from a
   customer-requirement interview with Janis. Confirmed with Janis before
   step 2 begins — a separate confirmation gate from step 2's own.
2. **`.claude/SKILL_product_design_skeleton.md`** — the FIRST skill file
   read after the scope file exists (before rules-dimensions.md, before
   any component-sizing conversation, before the first cc prompt; its own
   PREREQUISITE section points back to step 1). Its 3 worksheets are
   completed IN ORDER, all consuming the scope file's content directly,
   and confirmed with Janis together as one gate, separate from step 1's:
   a. **Skeleton Definition Worksheet** — Top-Down Skeleton Layout + Datum
      Reference Frame (Primary/Secondary/Tertiary) + Parent-Child design
      discipline (coordinate reference — "where is everything,
      geometrically")
   b. **BOM Subassembly Tree** (added 2026-07-07) — parts/subassembly
      hierarchy, a DIFFERENT artifact from the Skeleton, seeds that
      product's `PART_MANIFEST.md`
   c. **Kinetic Dual-View table** (added 2026-07-07) — every moving part
      from the BOM tree gets BOTH end states (open/closed, in/out, etc.)
      established as explicit toggles from its first committed version,
      not added later
3. First cc prompt written, standard coding/debug loop begins.

**Grandfather clause, Janis-directed, explicit: VM-01 and PR-01 are NOT
retrofitted to this system.** Both continue under the existing
DATUM_*/`.claude/SKILL_reference_point_first.md` convention. This applies
to later/new products only.

